Dear Dave,I do hope I can visit ECT more often as I can meet many good friends and learn a lot from them. Iâ€™m still gambling in the Taiwan casino and still alive. Thanks.1.	Both institutional and individual investors trade local index options (such as TXO, TEO, and TFO) actively. The underlying securities of these options are indexes, such as Taiwan Stock Exchange Capitalization Weighted Stock Index (TAIEX or TX), Taiwan Stock Exchange Electronic Sector Index (TE) and Taiwan Stock Exchange Finance Sector Index (TF). Some professional institutions may trade them for hedging purpose but most local individuals are believed to trade for speculation. In general, these individuals are young with financial knowledge, and trade stocks, index options and index futures via office computers. Retail investors may sometimes trade those 30 plus stock options, but I believe the options market makers account for more than 90% of the turnovers of these stock options. These stock options are poorly designed by the Taiwan Futures Exchange, so that their turnovers and open interests have remained very light since they were introduced several years ago. Ironically, most market makers are forced to make minimal required trades per month on these stock options so as to keep their profitable status as the market makers of index options (TXO, TEO, and TFO).2.	Those 30 plus stock options are options on stocks, such as options on China Steel, options on Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing Company, etc. There is no any listing futures on individual stock yet. This may explain, to a certain degree, why the local index options are successful but the stock options are not. You know that the index futures are actively traded in Taiwan. It seems that every investor is crazy about betting on indexes. 3.	You can find the information of 30 plus stock options in both Chinese and English by visiting the website of Taiwan Futures Exchange (Taifex) at www.taifex.com.tw. For example, if we want to find the open interests of options on Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing Company (Code: AGO), please enter the Taifex website and select the followings: English version > Market Data > Options > Daily Market Report > select the year, month and date > Send Query. I believe you will find lots of useful information about Taiwanâ€™s futures and options market from this website.The main stock market in Taiwan is managed by the Taiwan Stock Exchange Corporation. Both Chinese and English information are available from its website at www.tse.com.tw. 4.	Iâ€™m not familiar with the commodity spot and derivatives markets. I donâ€™t know exactly how the Chinese Petroleum Corporation, Taiwan (or CPC, Taiwan) hedges its spot position. It seems that the company makes lots of forward contracts on a regular basis, based on local news reports. However, Iâ€™m not sure if they deal with oil producers directly or trade futures contracts from futures markets. Sorry!Please let me know if you have any further questions about Taiwanâ€™s financial markets. Iâ€™ll try my best and I believe lots of financial experts at ECT will back me up, if I do not answer well. Finger


    	    	
