Dave,Your job must be very exciting and full of challenges, right? It reminds me the book: â€œMy Life as a Quant: Reflections on Physics and Financeâ€ by Emanuel Derman. He worked for Goldman as well. Your extended system with the function of real-time strategy recommendation will definitely benefit commodity traders a lot!  I witnessed the power of such system while working with my teammates on market making Taiwanâ€™s stock indexes options. Our system allows both traders and mid-office risk managers to monitor the individual/aggregated VaRs and Greeks of tradersâ€™ positions on a real-time basis. It also requests those traders, who have exceeded their risk exposure lines, offset/adjust their positions before market closing so as to meet the requirements of risk management. This system enables our traders to efficiently and precisely trade index options and hedge through index futures/index options/stock baskets. It also reduces lots of communication works between traders and risk managers as both parties monitor the same system during trading hours and speak the same language while communicating. Based on this experience, I do believe that such type of system will also work well for commodity derivatives trading.Taiwanâ€™s major securities firms have improved their financial engineering works and electronic trading systems a lot, following the booming of local index options starting from around 1999/2000. Some have provided their clients with online options trading simulators to educate themselves and encourage more trading as well. These systems are basically quite advanced and sophisticated. They have actually become a common sales kit of Taiwanâ€™s securities firms for attracting derivatives clients. However, according to my understanding, the benefit of providing these online simulators seems to be limited. Why? Most of their clients are retail investors who trade options for speculation with a limited fund size. These retail investors tend to neglect the risk as they trade options just for gambling. Some may pay attention to it, but unfortunately limited funds are likely to prohibit them from implementing complicated hedging strategies.  I think the system/tool with real-time strategy recommendation will benefit options proprietary trading desk of securities firms/investment banks/funds and professional institutional investors. But it may not be a good idea to target retail investors in Taiwan. However, as other markets may have different investor structures. I would recommend you having more feedbacks from other experts, such as Gina, our Queen of risk management.Finger


    	    	
	    2007/07/30 16:52






